thread.title_full: Narayana Vidyalayam to host CBSE West Zone taekwon-do championship - The Times of India

author: Suhas Nayse
title: Narayana Vidyalayam to host CBSE West Zone taekwon-do championship
text:
NAGPUR: Narayana Vidyalayam will be hosting the CBSE West Zone Taekwon-Do Championship from September 30 to October 3 on their school premises, Chinch Bhuvan, Wardha Road.
Addressing the press conference here on Monday, Col UK Chembath, director academics and administration, Nairsons Education Society, informed that the four-day meet will see the participation of around 800 boys and girls, vying for the honours in 30 different weight categories in two sections -- U-14 and U-19.
"Around 100 school teams from nine states including Gujarat, Goa, Rajasthan, Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh and Maharashtra will take part. Earlier in 2008-09, our school had successfully hosted the CBSE Chess Nationals and then CBSE West Zone Taekwon-Do C'ship in 2010-11," said Chembath.
Narayana Vidyalayam has been dominating the West Zone tourney for the last six years. "This time also we are expecting to emerge West Zone champions. Coach Pravin Dhande has been putting in lot of efforts," said Chembath.
The meet will be inaugurated on Wednesday at 8.30 am, while the prize distribution function will take place on October 3 at 4 pm. Principal of the school Mala Chembath will lead the organizing committee.
